# SSL Zertifikat erneuern (IIS) 

1. Start the IIS Manager 

2. Select the server name 

3. Open Server Certificates 

4. ![](data:image/png;base64,)

5. In the Actions pane select Create Certificate Request 

6. Fill out the form. The common name is the primary DNS name you will use for your website. 

7. You can submit additional DNS names later if needed 

8. In the Actions pane select Create Certificate Request 

9. Fill out the form. The common name is the primary DNS name you will use for your website. 

10. You can submit additional DNS names later if needed 

11. ![](data:image/png;base64,)

12. Set the Key length to 2048 

13. Save the certificate request on a local drive. 

14. Create a ticket via this link: <https://swatchgroupservices.service-now.com/esc?id=sc_cat_item&sys_id=c38fa613870b4550065585d30cbb352c> 
![](data:image/png;base64,)
1. You will revive the certificate by Email or in the Ticket 

2. Start the IIS Manager 

3. Select the server name 

4. Open Server Certificates 

5. Select in the Action menu Complete Certificate Request 

6. Browse the path to the certificate and enter a friendly name 

7. The old and the new certificates are listed in the Server certificate section on IIS. 

8. That the new certificate will be used by the website you need to change the https binding and select the new certificate to use. 

9. ![](data:image/png;base64,)

10. As cleanup when the website works with the new certificate you can remove the old from Server Certificates 

 

Bindinga certificate to a website in IIS means that you are activating the installed digital certificate and associating it with a particular website, port, and/or IP Address. Binding in IIS can be performed by following these simple steps. (These instructions assume that you have already[installed](https://www.ssl.com/how-to/install-an-ssl-tls-certificate-in-iis-10/)your certificate in IIS.) 

1. Start IIS Manager. StartIIS Manager. One quick way to do this is by opening theRuncommand, then typinginetmgrand clicking theOKbutton. 

![Run window](data:image/png;base64,)

2. Select website. In theConnectionspane on the left side of the window, navigate to theServerandSiteyou wish to bind the certificate to. 

![Select server and website](data:image/png;base64,)

3. Open bindings. In theActionspane on the right, clickBindings 

![Click Bindings](data:image/png;base64,)

4. Click Add Click theAddbutton. 

![Click Add...](data:image/png;base64,)

5. Select binding type. TheAdd Site Bindingwindow will open. ForType, selecthttps. 

![Select type](data:image/png;base64,)

6. Select IP address. ForIP address, selectAll Unassigned, or the sites IP address. 

![select IP address](data:image/png;base64,)

7. Enter port. ForPort, enter443. 

![Port](data:image/png;base64,)

8. Select certificate Select the desired certificate from theSSL certificatedrop-down menu. 

![select certificate](data:image/png;base64,)

9. View certificate details. You can use theViewbutton to get details about the selected certificate. 

![View certificate details](data:image/png;base64,)

10. Require Server Name Indication (SNI) if necessary. If you are serving more than one domain name from the same IP address, enter it in theHost namefield and check theRequire Server Name Indicationbox. If not, you can safely leave these blank. 

![Host name and SNI](data:image/png;base64,)

11. Close Add Site Binding window. Click theOKbutton to close the window. 

![OK button](data:image/png;base64,)

12. Close Site Bindings window. Verify that the binding has been added, then close theSite Bindingswindow by clicking theClosebutton. 

![OK button](data:image/png;base64,)

13. Edit existing binding (if necessary). You may can also edit an existing binding. To do this, simply select the item and click Edit. You can change the port, the IP Address, the host name, and the certificate to use. 

![Edit binding](data:image/png;base64,)

 

Aus <<https://www.ssl.com/how-to/binding-in-iis-10/>>

# Automatische Zertifizierungserneuerung

Wir schlagen vor, dass Renata die Zertifikate jeweils selbstndig erneuern kann ohne die Mithilfe von Autexis.

Dazu mssen folgende Schritte gemacht werden:

1. Erstellung der Zertifikate, spezifisch fr Test- oder Produktiv-System (issued to: renata-mestest.swatchgroup.net fr das Testsystem und renata-mes.swatchgroup.net fr das Produktivsystem)

2. Testsystem GDC03425: Ablegen der Zertifikate unter D:\DEV\keys als certificate.pem und key.pem. Die beiden Files vor dem Ersetzen in den backup-Ordner kopieren, damit im Fehlerfall auf diese zurckgegriffen werden kann.  
   ![](file:///tmp/lu3442292btke.tmp/lu3442292btn1_tmp_fb3bc595.png)

Produktivsystem GDC03424: Ablegen der Zertifikate unter D:\DEV\keys als renata-mes.swatchgroup.net.pem und renata-mes.swatchgroup.net\_key.pem. Die beiden Files vor dem Ersetzen in den backup-Ordner kopieren, damit im Fehlerfall auf diese zurckgegriffen werden kann.  
![](file:///tmp/lu3442292btke.tmp/lu3442292btn1_tmp_76ffe5ec.png)

3. Neustart des MES-Service: Da der Service jeden Abend kurz nach Mitternacht neu startet kann dieser Schritt weggelassen werden. Alternativ kann dies auch durch einen Neustart des Servers gemacht werden.
